They fired a Taser stun-gun at a 28-year-old man to subdue him before arresting him. They also arrested a man aged 24. In a street in nearby Charlton officers fired a Taser at a 21-year-old suspect.

All were arrested on suspicion of conspiracy to commit murder and remained in custody last night.Meanwhile detectives from the Met’s Counter Terrorism Command were granted extra time to question Abu Nusaybah, 31, who was arrested at the BBC following an interview he did on the its Newsnight programme on Friday.

He was held on suspicion of the commission, preparation or instigation of acts of terrorism. The arrest was not directly linked to Drummer Rigby’s death.

On TV Nusaybah claimed Adebolajo had been approached by MI5 six months ago and asked to work for the security service.

